%S A398168 1,2,4,5,6,9,10,12,13,14,18,20,21,22,25,28,29,30,33,34,36,37,38,41,42,
%T A398168 45,46,50,52,57,58,60,61,65,66,68,69,70,73,76,77,78,82,84,85,86,90,92,
%U A398168 93,94,100,101,102,105,106,109,110,113,114,117,118,121,122,126,129,130
%N A398168 Cubefree numbers k such that k+1 is squarefree.
%C A398168 The asymptotic density of this sequence is d = Product_{p prime} (1 - 1/p^2 - 1/p^3) = 0.479145344433396245631... . The number of terms not exceeding x is d * x + O(x^(2/3+eps)), where eps > 0 (Srichan et al., 2026, p. 3, Corollary 1.2).
%H A398168 Amiram Eldar, <a href="/A398168/b398168.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A398168 Teerapat Srichan, Nithi Rungtanapirom, and Saeree Wananiyakul, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1051/ita/2026022">On the distribution of consecutive M-free integers</a>, RAIRO - Theoretical Informatics and Applications, Vol. 60 (2026), Article 22.
%t A398168 freeQ[m_, k_] := freeQ[m, k] = AllTrue[FactorInteger[m][[;; , 2]], # < k &];
%t A398168 Select[Range[130], freeQ[#, 3] && freeQ[#+1, 2] &]
%o A398168 (PARI) isfree(m, k) = #select(x -> x >= k, factor(m)[,2]) == 0;
%o A398168 isok(m) = isfree(m, 3) && isfree(m+1, 2);
%Y A398168 Subsequence of A004709 and A340152.
%Y A398168 A007674 is a subsequence.
%Y A398168 Cf. A005117.
